snippet: DeMar DeRozan scored 34 points and Jonas Valanciunas had his eighth double-double with 19 points and 12 rebounds as the Toronto Raptors won their season-high sixth straight game, 115-109 over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night....
lead_paragraph: DeMar DeRozan scored 34 points and Jonas Valanciunas had his eighth double-double with 19 points and 12 rebounds as the Toronto Raptors won their season-high sixth straight game, 115-109 over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.

headline.main: DeRozan Scores 34 to Send Raptors Past Celtics, 115-109
headline.print_headline: DeRozan Scores 34 to Send Raptors Past Celtics, 115-109
